The paper deals with a variant of the capacitated vehicle routing problem, which is a classic problem in operations research and optimization. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The paper also presents an approximation algorithm, which involves the use of heuristics and optimization techniques, making it relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of scheduling and partitioning, which is related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
